  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of the diversity of cultural expressions, in particular through the effective implementation of the 2005 Convention</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over the past years, the countries of the San Jose cluster Office (Costa Rica, El Salvador, Honduras, Nicaragua and Panama) have shown increased interest in the field of cultural and creative industries and its contribution for sustainable development, while continuing to request capacity building and support to implement the 2005 Convention. To this end, the Culture Sector will provide technical support to Member States the elaboration of quadrennial periodic reports as well in the presentation of projects to the International Fund for Cultural Diversity (IFCD). Moreover, launching events of the Monitoring Global Report 2021 will provide the opportunity to raise awareness and reflect on the implementation of the Convention.</narrative>
  </description>
